title: lotus_eater
body:
The story of Lotus Eater has been in the works for over seven years, and we have been actively working on the story's art concepts for the past five years.

Lotus Eater: Ruination is the first of six main installments of the Lotus Eater story. From LE:R to the very final installment, each detail has been meticulously planned so that each of the six main arcs are woven together in ways that will make the reader want to revisit each installment again and again as new information comes to light.

Our ultimate goal is to create a Lotus Eater video game series based on our stories. Before that, we plan to distribute each installment as a printed novel, and later possibly as a series of graphic novels.

title: alan_grant
body: Alan Grant is a fictional character in the [[Jurassic Park]] franchise. He is a paleontologist and is introduced in Michael Crichton's 1990 novel Jurassic Park, which began the franchise. Crichton based Grant on the paleontologist Jack Horner who was by happenstance technical advisor for the movies. Director Steven Spielberg helmed the 1993 film adaptation, and several actors were considered for the role of Grant. It ultimately went to Sam Neill, becoming one of his most popular roles. Spielberg gave the character a dislike of children, and put him in a relationship with [[Ellie_Sattler_(jurassic_park)|Dr. Ellie Sattler]], a paleobotanist who is Grant's student in the novel. Sattler, portrayed by Laura Dern, wants to start a family with Grant, who is resistant to the idea.

title: spike_spiegel
body:
The main character of [[Cowboy Bebop]].

A bounty hunter with an affinity for [i]jeet kune do[/i], he hunts down criminals who escape the grasp of the Inter-Solar System Police (ISSP) with the help of his partner, former Ganymede policeman [[Jet Black]] on the ship known as the Bebop. Spike does not always succeed in getting a bounty, and his penchant for causing massive destruction when in pursuit of a bounty head means that the bounties that he and Jet do get do not last long.

Spike also has a hidden past that involves the Red Dragon, a crime syndicate modeled on the Chinese Triads, and in particular the ruthless assassin known as [[vicious_(cowboy_bebop)|Vicious]]. Also figuring big into Spike's past is the mysterious woman known as [[julia_(cowboy_bebop)|Julia]], who Spike and Vicious both loved.

Spike's weapon of choice is an [[IWI Jericho 941]], and when chasing bounty heads, his vehicle of choice is the [[Swordfish II]], an Asteroid racer outfitted with four machine guns, missile pylons, and a plasma cannon.

Voiced in Japan by Kōichi Yamadera and in America dub by Steven Jay Blum.

title: arepa
body:
Arepa is a type of food made of ground maize dough, originating from pre-Columbian northern region of South America, and is notable in the cuisines of [[Colombia]] and [[Venezuela]].

It is eaten daily in those countries and can be served with accompaniments such as cheese, cuajada (fermented milk), various meats, chicken, avocado, and diablito. It can also be split to make sandwiches. Sizes, maize types, and added ingredients vary its preparation. Arepas can also be found in the Canary Islands. It is similar in shape to the Mexican gordita and the Salvadoran pupusa.

The word "arepa" comes from the indigenous term "erepa", which means "corn" in the language of the Cumanagoto people.

The software was updated for VOCALOID4 in 2017, and was subsequently released alongside [[yumemi nemu (vocaloid)|Yumemi Nemu]].

Said to be designed to sell to "moe" and otaku based culture, she is meant to sound cute. She was illustrated by [[Watanabe Akio]]. She has [[purple hair]] (in [[twintails]]) and [[purple eyes]]. Her features show her with a single [[fang]] tooth and [[blush stickers]]. title: adachi_to_shimamura
body:
A light novel series by Iruma Hitoma (入間人間) that centers around the friendship between two high-school girls, [[Adachi Sakura|Adachi]] and [[Shimamura Hougetsu|Shimamura]]. The story outlines their everyday events and contains mild [[yuri]] themes. It began as a series in Vol. 28 of 電撃文庫MAGAZINE (Dengeki Bunko Magazine) in March 2013. Since then, ten volumes have been published by ASCII Media Works with [[Ousaka Nozomi|Non]] (のん) as the illustrator.

There are two manga adaptions; a 3 volume 2013 one illustrated by [b]Mani[/b], which was serialized online via Square Enix's Gangan Online website, and the other, an ongoing adaptation that began in 2019 with illustrations by [[Yuzuhara moke]]. There is also a 12 episode anime adaption by [i]Tezuka Productions[/i] which aired Fall of 2020.

title: mega_mawile
body:
The [[mega pokemon|Mega-Evolved]] form of [[Mawile]].

Type: Steel/Fairy
Ability: Huge Power
Height: 100 cm / 3'3"
Weight: 23.5 kg / 51.8 lbs

Mega Mawile looks similar to its non Mega-Evolved form, except it has pink colorations and markings on its body (while the markings on its head stay black). It grows over a foot (0.4 meters) in height, becomes more bulky in appearance, and grows a second jaw on its head (with both jaws becoming curved and jagged). In battle, this gives it the ability [b]Huge Power[/b], which effectively (with the slight boost to it base attack from Mega Evolving) gives it the highest attack stat in the entire game. This, along with its Fairy typing, has spawned a multitude of jokes, stating that Mawile is not only a Dragon slayer, but a world destroyer as well.

title: kurapika
body:
One of the main characters from [[Hunter x Hunter]].

A Blacklist Hunter and member of the Kurta Clan, being the only remaining member so far, Kurapika vows to avenge his fallen clan by destroying the Phantom Troupe after the latter massacred his clan for their "Scarlet Eyes", thus being his ultimate goal in becoming a Hunter.

He is usually calm, smart, and reticent, but becomes more wrathful and callous when threatened, attributing to his tragic past. This makes him impulsive sometimes, despite doing so for the sake of protecting his friends and avenging his clan.

Voiced by [[Hidaka Noriko]] (Pilot OVA), [[Kaida Yuki]] (1999), [[Sawashiro Miyuki]] (2011), and [[Erika Harlacher]] (2011; EN).

h4.Appearance
Kurapika has an [[androgynous]] appearance. He is a short [[blonde hair|blonde haired]] young man with [[brown eyes]] which turn [[red eyes|scarlet red]] in some occasions. His outfit is usually a [[tabard]] with reddish hem and a white [[white shirt|shirt]] and [[white pants|pants]]. His footwear is a blue-colored [[flats]].

title: ganesha_(mythology)
body:
In [[Hindu mythology]], [b]Ganesha[/b] (or [b]Ganesh[/b]) is the [[elephant]]-headed god of arts, knowledge, and willpower. He is one of the most well-known Hindi gods and is widely worshipped in several Hindu sects. In most traditions, Ganesha is the son of [[Shiva (mythology)|]] and [[Parvati (mythology)|]].

In most traditions, the story of how Ganesha got his elephant head usually revolves around how his father Shiva accidentally beheaded him either by his earth-scorching third eye or his [[chakram]] and used an elephant's head as a replacement. Another story says that Shiva found Ganesha too alluring, so he gave him an elephant head and [[fat|large belly]] to prevent future trouble.

title: basic_instinct_(movie)
body: A 1992 neo-noir, erotic thriller Western film directed by Paul Verhoeven. It follows police detective Nick Curran (played by Michael Douglas) on a serial murder case, who gets sexually involved with the prime suspect, Catherine Tramell (played by Sharon Stone), a cunning and manipulative author. The film is famous and infamous for its overt depictions of sex and violence, which were highly explicit for its time. It's most famous for its interrogation scene, in which Tramell intentionally flashes herself while switching [[crossed legs]] in her seat.

body:
[i]Flint, a tribal warrior, is the pure embodiment of power.[/i]

A playable Guard Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real name: Kemar

h4. Profile

A Sargon tribal warrior from the jungle of Acahualla, she joined Rhodes Island on [[Blaze (arknights)|]]'s recommendation.

She comes from a Liberi tribe of smaller stature and frailer constitution, as such she wants to challenge stronger people in order to mold and improve herself, until she can beat them with her [[boxing gloves]].

She likes lushly colored flowers and gives a hand at [[Perfumer (arknights)|]]'s greenhouse.

Her motif is based on the white-necked jacobin.

Her [[voice actor]]s are [[Yamamura Hibiku (voice actor)|]] (Japanese), and Hou Xiaofei (Chinese). Her art designer is [[aZLing]]

title: taoist_rope
body:
The "Daoist/Taoist":[/wiki_pages/taoism] robe (道袍) is a traditional garment worn by Daoist practitioners, symbolizing their spiritual beliefs and cultural heritage. These robes are typically long and flowing, crafted from silk or cotton, and often adorned with symbols such as the "Eight Trigrams (bagua, 八卦)":[/wiki_pages/bagua] or "Yin-Yang (阴阳)":[/wiki_pages/yin_yang] to reflect Daoist philosophy. Designed for both ritual and daily use, they emphasize simplicity, harmony, and the connection between humans and nature, key tenets of Daoism. The robes vary in color and design, with different styles signifying the wearer's role, sect, or spiritual attainment.

h4. See also

* [[Taoism]]

body:
A [[half note|half]] [[musical note|note]] that has at least one dot placed to the right of it. The dot denotes that the note's length is increased by half of its original value. In general, a note can have up to three dots. Subsequent dots add progressively halved value.

Not to be confused with [[staccato]], where the dot is placed above or below a note.

title: chris_(konosuba)
body:
[b]Chris[/b] is a female character in the [[Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo!|KonoSuba]] series. She is a thief and a member of the Eris Church who teaches [[satou_kazuma|Kazuma]] many thief skills and was [[darkness_(konosuba)|Darkness's]] first adventuring companion. She is a good friend of both Darkness and Kazuma.

Chris is a teenage girl with a light complexion and [[purple eyes]]. She has [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair|silver/grey hair]] and two strands of hair ([[sidelocks]]) framing her face with a piece of hair pointing out from her fringe ([[side ahoge]]). She also has a [[scar on cheek|scar]] on her right cheek. Most likely due to her tomboyish and outgoing nature, along with her [[small breasts|small]] (almost [[flat chest|flat]]) chest and short hair, she is often mistaken for a boy.

Chris usually wears a fairly revealing outfit. Her outfit consists of a light blue ([[aqua scarf|aqua]]) [[scarf]], a short [[green cape]] which goes down to her elbows, a pair of [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]] with normal [[brown gloves]] layered over them, [[short shorts|short]] [[denim shorts|blue jean-shorts]], [[white thighhighs]] with a [[blue trim|blue trimming]], [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]], and a bikini-like grey [[crop top|top]]. [spoiler]Ever since her first run-in with Kazuma, Chris has worn [[black leggings]] in case her [[panties]] are stolen again.[/spoiler] She also wears diamond-shaped blue [[earrings]] and usually has an enchanted [[dagger]] fastened to her waist on her back.

title: chef_(south_park)
body: Chef Jerome McElroy, often referred to as just "Chef", is a fictional character on the Comedy Central series [[South Park]] who was voiced by Isaac Hayes. A cafeteria worker at the local elementary school in the town of South Park, Colorado, Chef is generally portrayed as more intelligent than the other adult residents of the town, and understanding to the children. His advice is often sought by the show's core group of child protagonists —[[Stan Marsh]], [[Kyle Broflovski]], [[Eric Cartman]], and [[Kenny McCormick]] — as he is the only adult they completely trust. He frequently gives completely honest advice without considering whether it is appropriate for children, usually in the non sequitur form of a lascivious soul song.

title: johann_sebastian_bach
body: Johann Sebastian Bach (31 March [O.S. 21 March] 1685 – 28 July 1750) was a [[germany|German]] composer and musician of the late Baroque period. He is known for his prolific output across a variety of instruments and forms, including orchestral music such as the Brandenburg Concertos; solo instrumental works such as the cello suites and sonatas and partitas for solo violin; keyboard works such as the Goldberg Variations and The Well-Tempered Clavier; organ works such as the Schubler Chorales and the Toccata and Fugue in D minor; and choral works such as the St Matthew Passion and the Mass in B minor. Since the 19th century Bach Revival, he has been generally regarded as one of the greatest composers in the history of Western music.

body: The TIE/sa bomber, formally known as the TIE Surface Assault Bomber and also known as the TIE/sa tactical bomber or simply the TIE bomber, was a bombing variant of the TIE fighter series used by the Galactic Empire in the [[Star Wars]] series. title: spider-man_(2099)
body: Spider-Man 2099 is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]]. The character was created by Peter David and Rick Leonardi in 1992 for the Marvel 2099 comic book line, and he is a futuristic re-imagining of the original [[Spider-Man]] created by Stan Lee and Steve Ditko. His true identity is Miguel O'Hara, an Irish-Mexican geneticist living in Nueva York (a renamed New York City) in the year 2099 who attempts to re-create the abilities of the original Spider-Man in other people and later suffers a related accident that causes half of his DNA to be rewritten with a spider's genetic code.

title: silent_hill_1
body: Silent Hill is a 1999 survival horror game developed by Team Silent, a group within Konami Computer Entertainment Tokyo, and published by Konami. As the first installment in the [[silent hill (series)|Silent Hill]] video game series, the game was released exclusively for the PlayStation. Silent Hill uses a third-person view with real-time rendering of 3D environments. To mitigate the limitations of the console hardware, developers used fog and darkness to obscure the graphics and hide pop-ins, which, in turn, helped establish the game's atmosphere and mystery. Unlike earlier survival horror games that focused on protagonists with combat training, the player character of Silent Hill is an "everyman".

Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆☆☆]]. Her extremely unique voice and realistic voice acting instantly made her one of Cookie's most popular characters and the breakout star of the entire Kuso series. Identifiable by her [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] with [[blunt bangs]], her [[pink apron]] with her [[character name|name]] [[clothes writing|on it]], and [[holding_grater|holding]] a [[hand grater]] used to make [[carrot shirishiri]]. title: swiss_guard
body:
The [b]Papal Swiss Guard[/b](also known as the Papal Guards) is an elite military unit from [[Switzerland]] that have protected the [[Pope]] since 1506. 

While the name "Swiss Guard" originally meant an elite bodyguard unit of Swiss soldiers that protected some European Monarchs in the past, today, the name now refers to the Papal Swiss Guard in Vatican City ever since Switzerland banned the practice of their citizens working in foreign armies since 1848 with the Vatican being an exception.

The Papal Swiss Guard are famous for their renaissance era uniforms and wielding halberds while on duty.  As their name reveals, only Swiss, Catholic males who are single, around the ages 19 to 30 and served in the Swiss Armed Forces may join the Papal Swiss Guard.

The Bomber Bill rename is seemingly being kept for the foreseeable future, with its usage in the [[The Super Mario Bros. Movie]] in 2023 and [[Super Mario Party Jamboree]] in 2024.

title: kite_shield
body: A type of tall medieval European [[shield]] with a distinctive pointed almond shape (hence also sometimes called an [i]almond shield[/i]). Commonly associated with the Battle of Hastings (1066) due to its ubiquity on the Bayeux tapestry. Not to be confused with a [i]heater shield[/i], which is the classic smaller point-at-the-bottom shield shape commonly seen in heraldry, early issues of [i][[Captain America]][/i], and United States Interstate Highway System signage.

title: creeper
body:
A [[monster]] from the game [[Minecraft]]. It is one of the most dangerous hostile mobs in the game. Spawns in the Overworld on light level of zero. Its only attack is to [[explosion|explode]], fatally damaging the player, and destroying nearby blocks. This, combined with its nearly silent footsteps and its only making its trademark "Tsss" (or "シュー" as it's known in Japanese) when it is about to explode—has given it a notorious reputation for taking players completely by surprise.

Amongst the Japanese community it has earned the nickname "匠" or "たくみ (Takumi)", which translates to "Craftsman." Being one of the most memorable and original mobs in the game, it has become a kind of mascot for Minecraft.

It is the primary source of gunpowder. A creeper surviving a lightning strike will turn into the more powerful [[charged creeper]]. If killed by a [[skeleton (minecraft)|]] or [[stray (minecraft)|]], it will drop a [[music disc (minecraft)|]].

title: madou_meihou-sou_no_kousatsu
body:
[b]A Study in the Dubious Meihou-sou[/b]

[quote]The story begins when a new minute Singularity is detected...

Structured differently than any yet seen, the Singularity contains myriad locations and symbols from various time periods all in one place.
It's almost like like being in a movie.
In this world, created from the bitter frustration of a filmmaker who left a movie unfinished, completing the production is of the greatest importance.

Amid a flurry of speculation about the film's ending, one can only wonder how this story will conclude when the mystery is finally laid to rest.
[/quote]

An event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] guest-written by Madoi Ban which was later adapted into a novel illustrated by [[Honjou Raita]]. In it, Chaldea visits a singularity where they must finish the production of a murder-mystery themed film. [[Murasaki Shikibu (fate)|]] ends up penning the draft for the story, but the ending (and who the mastermind is) remains up in the air until production is concluded. This event also introduces a [[Bartholomew Roberts (fate)|stray servant]] who can't remember his true name, who goes by his character's name of Salazar.

title: ian_malcolm
body: Dr. Ian Malcolm is a mathematician who specializes in a branch of mathematics known as "Chaos Theory". Malcolm is the tritagonist of the [[Jurassic Park]] franchise, serving as the tritagonist of Jurassic Park, the main protagonist of The Lost World: Jurassic Park, one of the three unseen overarching protagonists of [[Jurassic World]], a minor character in Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom, and one of the three overarching protagonists of Jurassic World: Dominion. Malcolm appears in both novels by Michael Crichton. Malcolm serves as the mouthpiece of Crichton, who called Malcolm the "ironic commentator" on the action. In the movies, Malcolm is portrayed by Jeff Goldblum. Malcolm also appeared in most other Jurassic media like comics, video games and toy lines.

Many, such as those inspired by [[Dungeons & Dragons]] tend to have [[colored skin]] in various tones of [[blue skin|blue]], [[grey skin|grey]], or [[purple skin| purple]]. Others like the [[Dark Eldar]] from [[Warhammer 40k]] tend to have extremely [[pale skin|pale]] or [[white skin]]. Typical dark elves in many Japanese copyrights instead just have [[dark skin]].

title: medic_(isekai_mokushiroku_mynoghra)
body:
One of Mynoghra's normal units produced by Eternal Nation's Clinic facility. They're tall humanoid creatures wrapped entirely in black with a [[plague doctor]] motif. Concealed beneath their robes they have large eyes, shriveled flesh, bent limbs, swollen lumps with darkened skin and ferocious claws, as they're actually Brain Eaters. They're obsessed with humans to the point of wearing the raw flesh they skin off their victims and they refer to humans as "hueman". Contrary to their appearance, they're loud, cheerful and use overly exaggerated gestures.

Normal units don't have unique names, but Takuto named three Medics as Ichiro, Jiro and Saburo.

title: wario_land:_shake_it!
body:
The final entry in the [i][[Wario Land]][/i] series and developed primarily outside of [[Nintendo]] by Good-Feel, released on the [[Wii]].

The Shake Dimension is under peril due to the marauding of the [[Shake King]] and kidnapping of [[Queen Merelda]]. [[Wario]] is uninterested about the plight of the escaped [[Merfle_(wario_land)|]]'s homeworld until it's mentioned that the Shake King also stole the Bottomless Coin Sack, which Wario now wants for himself. Making a deal, Wario has a change of heart and agrees to help the Merfle to acquire this treasure.

Notable for bringing back a redesigned [[Captain Syrup]].

title: shop_owner_(wario_land)
body:
A character in [[Wario Land 4]]. A mysterious entity that runs the Item Shop before each Boss Door. 

The entity will use the items purchased to damage the boss preemptively before the battle begins. Some of the items purchased do not give you a physical item, but instead will have the Shop Owner transform into different creatures to do the damage themselves. These transformations are the [i]Black Dog[/i], the [i]Large Lips[/i], the [i]Big Fist[/i] and the [i]Black Dragon[/i].

h6.All items:
* Apple Bomb
* Blast Cannon
* Vizorman
* Bugle
* [[Black_Dog_(wario_land)|Black Dog]]
* [[Large_Lips_(wario_land)|Large Lips]]
* [[big_fist_(wario_land)|Big Fist]]
* [[black_dragon_(wario_land)|Black Dragon]]

You can also order a free "Smile", but it doesn't do anything. 

[spoiler]Its true identity is that of [[Princess Shokora]].[/spoiler]

title: azur_lane:_slow_ahead
body:
An [[Azur Lane]] slice-of-life manga by [[Hori (hori no su)|]], set around the schooling and daily adventures of the starter destroyer shipgirls [[Javelin (Azur Lane)|]], [[Ayanami (Azur Lane)|]], [[Laffey (Azur Lane)|]] and their advisor [[Z23 (Azur Lane)|]].

Adapted into an anime in early 2021 that is not only different in genre and emotional tone to the original [i]Azur Lane[/i] anime, but also made at least partly in-house, as Candybox has studio credit alongside Yostar Pictures. The series also features episode [[end card]]s drawn by fan artists.

Use this tag for the actual 4koma itself or for things referencing either the anime or 4koma (For example, [[North Carolina (Azur Lane)|North Carolina]]’s bunny suit from both, which predates [[North Carolina (The Heart's Desire) (Azur Lane)|The Heart's Desire]], would only count if it's black with the outfit tips down or black with her jacket over it). The tag can also be used for skins that originated in the 4koma before becoming available in the game, such as Javelin's [[Javelin (Slow Ahead!) (Azur Lane)|Slow Ahead!]] or the starters' fantasy/RPG-themed skins.

title: praise_the_sun
body:
[i]"The sun is a wondrous body, like a magnificent father! If only I could be so grossly incandescent..."[/i]

A pose involving stretching out one's arms upwards and tilting one's head towards the sky, as if one was ready to embrace the sun. 

While this pose is most commonly associated with [[Dark Souls I|Dark Souls's]] [[Solaire of Astora]] and the Warriors of Sunlight, it first appeared in [[Demon's Souls]] as an alternate animation for casting miracles while equipping the Ring of Sincere Prayer.

The emoticon associated with it is [b]\o/[/b]. The Solaire specific version is [b]\[T]/[/b].

title: snake_eyes_(character)
body:
A character from the [[G.I. Joe]] toy line, comic books, cartoon and live action film series. 

[b]Snake Eyes[/b] (also released as [b]Snake-Eyes[/b]) is one of the original and most known members of the G.I. Joe Team. 

A lone silent commando clad in a black outfit and mask, Snake Eyes is an expert in unorthodox [[martial arts]] and advanced [[close-quarters combat]], hand-to-hand combat, infiltration, stealth and firearms. He is one of the most prominent characters in the G.I. Joe franchise, having appeared in every series of the franchise since its inception. 

He never speaks and only communicates through hand gestures. To this day, nobody knows if he can actually say a word. 

Snake-Eyes debuted as an [[action figure]] in 1982. His figure is considered the most popular G.I. Joe toy ever, with 68 different versions released as of 2014.

He is portrayed by actor/stuntman "Ray Park":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ray_Park in the 2009 live-action film [i]"G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.I._Joe:_The_Rise_of_Cobra [/i] and the 2013 sequel [i]"G.I. Joe: Retaliation":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.I._Joe:_Retaliation].[/i]

title: chris_redfield
body:
[b]Chris Redfield[/b] is a Special Operations Agent (SOA) of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA), of which he is a founding member. Formerly, he served in the US Air Force; before moving on to law enforcement as a member of the RPD's Special Tactics And Rescue Service's (S.T.A.R.S.) Alpha Team. After S.T.A.R.S. were disbanded following the Raccoon City Incident, he and his partner, [[Jill Valentine]], became members of a Private Regional Biohazard Containment Unit (BCU), and took part in the fall of Umbrella in 2003. 

Chris is the older brother of [[Claire Redfield]] and one of few survivors of the mansion incident, during the Arklay Mountains outbreak in 1998. In addition to his qualification to pilot fixed-wing aircraft, Chris has been trained strictly in several fighting techniques like [[close-quarters combat]], is an expert in knife and firearm combat, and is also gifted with great accuracy.

Also notorious for punching a boulder in the climax of [[Resident Evil 5]].

h4.Appearance
Chris is a [[muscular male|muscular man]] with [[black hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. His appearance varies throughout the series.

* [[Resident Evil 1]]: Chris wears a [[police uniform]] with [[white shirt]], [[black pants]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[fingerless gloves]], and black boots.
* [[Resident Evil 5]]: Chris has a [[green shirt]], [[gloves]], [[grey pants]] and a [[green footwear|green shoes]]. His appearance changes noticeably, looking much more muscular compared to Resident Evil 1 .
* [[Resident Evil 6]]: Chris wears a similar outfit to the ones he wore in Resident Evil 5, albeit he sports a [[grey pants]], [[green shirt]], [[bulletproof vest]] and [[gloves]].
* [[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]: In Resident Evil 7: biohazard, Chris design changed to a less muscular body and a [[brown hair]], he sports a [[black jacket]], [[gloves]], [[black pants]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[black shoes]] and [[knee pads]]. 
* [[Resident Evil Village]]: Chris has a much more matured appearance in Resident Evil Village, he sports a [[black coat]] along with [[black shirt]], [[black pants]], [[gloves]] and black shoes.

h4. See also

* [[Chrisposting (meme)]]

title: chidejika
body:
Chidejika is a [[mascot]] created as a spokesperson for the [[Japan Commercial Broadcasters Association]] as a preparation for Japanese TV stations to switch to digital programming by July 24, 2011. Chidejika is an upright-walking deer wearing a yellow leotard.

The name actually means "terrestrial digitalization." The chi (地) means earth. Deji (デジ) is short for digital. Jika (ジカ) means deer. 

The mascot was created after the association dropped its original spokesperson, SMAP's Kusanagi Tsuyoshi, following his arrest for indecent exposure. Kusanagi was later reinstated, thus sharing the spokesperson position with Chidejika.
